Koopa Kid Time (After Turn).code:
; NAME: Koopa Kid Time (After Turn)
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct
; PARAM: Number|EventIndex

ADDIU SP SP -120
SW RA 116(SP)
SW S4 112(SP) ; Current Player's Struct
SW S0 108(SP) ; Player Index for Loop Counter
SW S3 104(SP) ; Equalized Coins / Chosen Player's Struct
SW S1 100(SP) ; Player's Coins 
SW S5 96(SP) ; Current Player's Coins
SW S7 92(SP) ; Flag Holder for Loops
SW S6 88(SP) ; Counter for Loop

;====================================================================
; IMPORTANT: This code is designed to replicate the Koopa Kid Space 
;            from Mario Party 7. If the EventIndex parameter is set to
;            0, it will randomize 1 of the following 6 events:
;			 (1) Turn player's next roll is cursed.
;			 (2) Equalize all player's coins. (Bowser Revolution)
;			 (3) Swap turn player's coins with a random player.
;			 (4) Swap turn player's position with a random player.
;			 (5) Shuffle the position of all players. (Bowser Shuffle)
;			 (6) Shuffle all player's items 
;			 
;            If you would rather use only 1 of these events, all you
;            have to do is set the EventIndex parameter to the
;            corresponding index listed in the parenthesis above.
;            While this event is made to be a landing event, it should
;            work fine as a passing event, too.
;			 
;			 At the bottom of the code you will find useful links and
;			 explanations for some technical things in the code.
;====================================================================

; Newly added code to load the current turn number and total turns
LUI T1 hi(current_turn)
ADDIU T1 T1 lo(current_turn) ; Loading address of current turn number
LBU T1 0(T1) ; Loading current turn number
LUI T0 hi(total_turns)
ADDIU T0 T0 lo(total_turns) ; Loading address of total turn number
LBU T0 0(T0) ; Loading total turn number

; Newly added code to hopefully only activate this every 4 turns
LI T2 4
DIVU T1 T2
MFHI T3
BNEZ T3 exit
NOP

LI A0 -1 ; Current Player
LI A1 -1 ; Idle Animation
JAL SetBoardPlayerAnimation ; in case some maniac wants to make this a passing event...
LI A3 2 ; Loop

JAL GetPlayerStruct ; Struct at V0
LI A0 -1 ; Current Player
MOVE S4 V0 ; Copy Struct to S4

JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x2A0 ; Koopa Kid Bark sfx

LUI A1 hi(Intro_Message)
JAL ShowMessage_Function ; Display and Close Message
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(Intro_Message)

LUI A1 hi(Intro2_Message)
JAL ShowMessage_Function ; Display and Close Message
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(Intro2_Message)

LI T0 EventIndex 
BEQZ T0 randomizeevent ; If 0, randomize which event happens
NOP
chooseevent:
LI T1 1 ; Space Shuffle Event Index
BEQ T0 T1 spaceshuffle ; If 1, shuffle everyone's position
NOP
LI T1 2 ; Revolution Event Index
BEQ T0 T1 revolution ; If 2, coin revolution
NOP
LI T1 3 ; Item Shuffle Event Index
BEQ T0 T1 itemshuffle ; If 3, shuffle everyone's items
NOP
LI T1 4 ; Revolution Event Index
BEQ T0 T1 revolution ; If 4, coin revolution
NOP
LI T1 5 ; Space Shuffle Event Index
BEQ T0 T1 spaceshuffle ; If 5, suffle everyone's position
NOP
J itemshuffle ; If none of the others, shuffle everyone's items
NOP

randomizeevent:
JAL GetRandomByte ; Number from 0-255 at V0
NOP
LI T0 6
DIVU V0 T0 ; Divide by 6 events
MFHI T0 ; Remainder of division (0-5)
J chooseevent
ADDIU T0 T0 1 ; Add 1 so it's 1-6

;================================================CURSED MUSHROOM EVENT

cursedmushroom:
LI T0 0x800CD0AF ; Address of Cursed Dice Flags
LBU T1 0(T0) ; Value of Cursed Dice Flags
LBU T2 29(S4) ; Current Player's Index
LI T3 1
SLLV T3 T3 T2 ; Shift Left by Player's Index
AND T4 T1 T3 ; T4 = 1 if player is cursed, 0 if not
BEQZ T4 cursedmushroom2 ; If not cursed, continue
NOP 

LI T5 EventIndex
BEQZ T0 randomizeevent ; If the creator chose to randomize the event, pick a different one.
NOP
J alreadycursed ; If set to curse only, generate message saying they're already cursed.
NOP

cursedmushroom2:
ADDU T1 T1 T3 ; Add player's curse flag
SB T1 0(T0) ; Store the new flag value
LBU T0 23(S4) ; Current Player's Status Flag
ADDIU T0 T0 2 ; Add Poison Mushroom Head Value
SB T0 23(S4) ; Store new Status Flag

JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x2A0 ; Koopa Kid Bark sfx

LUI A1 hi(Cursed_Message)
JAL ShowMessage_Function ; Display and Close Message
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(Cursed_Message)

JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0xD ; Cursed Mushroom sfx

LBU A0 29(S4) ; Current Player's Index
JAL SetBoardPlayerAnimationWithSound
LI A1 1 ; 0 = Happy, 1 = Sad

JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x2A0 ; Koopa Kid Bark sfx

LUI A1 hi(CurseExplanation_Message)
JAL ShowMessage_Function ; Display and Close Message
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(CurseExplanation_Message)

J goodbye
NOP

;=====================================================REVOLUTION EVENT

revolution:
JAL GetSumOfPlayerCoins ; Total Coins at V0
NOP
MOVE S0 V0 ; Copy to S0

BNEZ S0 revolution2 ; If there's at least 1 coin total, proceed
NOP

LI T0 EventIndex 
BEQZ T0 randomizeevent ; If the creator chose to randomize the event, pick a different one.
NOP
J nocoinsforrevolution
NOP

revolution2:
JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x2A0 ; Koopa Kid Bark sfx

LUI A1 hi(Revolution_Message)
JAL ShowMessage_Function ; Display and Close Message
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(Revolution_Message)

LI T0 4 
DIVU S0 T0 ; Divide by 4
MFLO S3 ; Coins to give back

LHU S5 10(S4) ; Current Player's Coins

LI S0 3 ; Start with Player 4
revolutionloop:
BLTZ S0 revolutionloop_exit ; exit loop once all players lose their coins
NOP

JAL GetPlayerStruct ; Struct at V0
MOVE A0 S0 ; Player Index
LHU S1 10(V0) ; Coins

MOVE A0 S0 ; Player's Index
JAL AdjustPlayerCoinsGradual 
SUBU A1 R0 S1 ; Coins

MOVE A0 S0 ; Player's Index
JAL 0x800E1F28 ; ShowPlayerCoinChangeHUD
SUBU A1 R0 S1 ; Coins

J revolutionloop
ADDIU S0 S0 -1 ; Subtract 1 to get next player

revolutionloop_exit:
JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 30 ; Frames

LI S0 3 ; Start with Player 4
revolutionloop2:
BLTZ S0 revolutionloop_exit2 ; exit loop once all players get their coins
NOP

MOVE A0 S0 ; Player Index
JAL AdjustPlayerCoinsGradual
MOVE A1 S3 ; Coins

MOVE A0 S0 ; Player Index
JAL 0x800E1F28 ; ShowPlayerCoinChangeHUD
MOVE A1 S3 ; Coins

J revolutionloop2
ADDIU S0 S0 -1

revolutionloop_exit2:
JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 30 ; Frames

SLT T0 S3 S5 ; T0 = 1 if the amount of coins is now lower
BNEZL T0 revolution3 ; If the player has less coins, sad animation
LI A1 1 ; Sad Index
LI A1 0 ; Happy animation if the player has more coins

revolution3:
JAL SetBoardPlayerAnimationWithSound
LBU A0 29(S4) ; Current Player's Index

J goodbye
NOP

;======================================================COIN SWAP EVENT

coinswap:
JAL GetSumOfPlayerCoins ; Total at V0
NOP

BNEZ V0 coinswap2 ; If there's at least 1 coin, continue
NOP

LI T0 EventIndex 
BEQZ T0 randomizeevent ; If the creator chose to randomize the event, pick a different one.
NOP
J nocoinsforrevolution
NOP

coinswap2:
JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x2A0 ; Koopa Kid Bark sfx

LUI A1 hi(CoinSwap_Message)
JAL ShowMessage_Function ; Display and Close Message
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(CoinSwap_Message)

coinswapreroll:
JAL GetRandomByte ; 0-255 Number at V0
NOP
LI T0 4
DIVU V0 T0 ; Divide by 4 to get other player
MFHI V0 ; Remainder of division at V0 (0-3)
LBU T0 29(S4) ; Current Player's Index
BEQ V0 T0 coinswapreroll ; If it's the current player, reroll
NOP

JAL GetPlayerStruct ; Struct at V0
MOVE A0 V0 ; Chosen Player's Index
MOVE S3 V0 ; Copy Struct to S3

LHU T0 10(S4) ; Current Player's Coins
SH T0 76(SP) ; Store in the Stack for future use
LHU T1 10(S3) ; Chosen Player's Coins
SH T1 72(SP) ; Store in the Stack for future use

LBU A0 29(S4) ; Current Player's Index
JAL AdjustPlayerCoinsGradual
SUBU A1 R0 T0 ; Subtract all Coins

LHU T0 76(SP) ; Load Current Player's Coins from the Stack
LBU A0 29(S4) ; Current Player's Index
JAL 0x800E1F28 ; ShowPlayerCoinChangeHUD
SUBU A1 R0 T0 ; Subtract all Coins
;====
LHU T0 72(SP) ; Load Chosen Player's Coins from the Stack
LBU A0 29(S3) ; Current Player's Index
JAL AdjustPlayerCoinsGradual
SUBU A1 R0 T0 ; Subtract all Coins

LHU T0 72(SP) ; Load Chosen Player's Coins from the Stack
LBU A0 29(S3) ; Current Player's Index
JAL 0x800E1F28 ; ShowPlayerCoinChangeHUD
SUBU A1 R0 T0 ; Subtract all Coins

JAL SleepProcess 
LI A0 45 ; Sleeps for 45 frames
;====
LBU A0 29(S4) ; Current Player's Index
JAL AdjustPlayerCoinsGradual
LHU A1 72(SP) ; Add chosen player's Coins

LBU A0 29(S4) ; Current Player's Index
JAL 0x800E1F28 ; ShowPlayerCoinChangeHUD
LHU A1 72(SP) ; Add chosen player's Coins
;====
LBU A0 29(S3) ; Current Player's Index
JAL AdjustPlayerCoinsGradual
LHU A1 76(SP) ; Add chosen player's Coins

LBU A0 29(S3) ; Current Player's Index
JAL 0x800E1F28 ; ShowPlayerCoinChangeHUD
LHU A1 76(SP) ; Add chosen player's Coins

JAL SleepProcess 
LI A0 30 ; Sleeps for 30 frames

LHU T0 76(SP) ; Current Player's Original Coin Amount
LHU T1 72(SP) ; Chosen Player's Original Coin amount
SLT T2 T1 T0 ; T0 = 1 if the amount of coins is now lower
BNEZL T2 coinswap3 ; If the player has less coins, sad animation
LI A1 1 ; Sad Index
LI A1 0 ; Happy animation if the player has more coins

coinswap3:
JAL SetBoardPlayerAnimationWithSound
LBU A0 29(S4) ; Current Player's Index

J goodbye
NOP

;=====================================================SPACE SWAP EVENT

spaceswap:
JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x2A0 ; Koopa Kid Bark sfx

LUI A1 hi(SpaceSwap_Message)
JAL ShowMessage_Function ; Display and Close Message
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(SpaceSwap_Message)

spaceswapreroll:
JAL GetRandomByte ; 0-255 Number at V0
NOP
LI T0 4
DIVU V0 T0 ; Divide by 4 to get other player
MFHI V0 ; Remainder of division at V0 (0-3)
LBU T0 29(S4) ; Current Player's Index
BEQ V0 T0 spaceswapreroll ; If it's the current player, reroll
NOP

JAL GetPlayerStruct ; Struct at V0
MOVE A0 V0 ; Chosen Player's Index
MOVE S3 V0 ; Copy Struct to S3

LI A0 1 ; Fade style (Circle)
JAL InitFade
LI A1 0 ; Fade type (out)

JAL PlaySound 
LI A0 0x107 ; Warp Block Sound Index

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 15 ; Frames

LUI T1 hi(CurrentPlayerSpaces_Array)
ADDIU T1 T1 lo(CurrentPlayerSpaces_Array)

LBU T0 15(S4) ; Current Player's Current Chain Index
SB T0 0(T1) ; Store in the Array
LBU T0 16(S4) ; Current Player's Current Chain Space Index
SB T0 1(T1) ; Store in the Array
LBU T0 17(S4) ; Current Player's Next Chain Index
SB T0 2(T1) ; Store in the Array
LBU T0 18(S4) ; Current Player's Next Chain Space Index
SB T0 3(T1) ; Store in the Array
LBU T0 21(S4) ; Current Player's Previous Chain Index
SB T0 4(T1) ; Store in the Array
LBU T0 22(S4) ; Current Player's Previous Chain Space Index
SB T0 5(T1) ; Store in the Array

LUI T1 hi(ChosenPlayerSpaces_Array)
ADDIU T1 T1 lo(ChosenPlayerSpaces_Array)

LBU T0 15(S3) ; Chosen Player's Current Chain Index
SB T0 0(T1) ; Store in the Array
LBU T0 16(S3) ; Chosen Player's Current Chain Space Index
SB T0 1(T1) ; Store in the Array
LBU T0 17(S3) ; Chosen Player's Next Chain Index
SB T0 2(T1) ; Store in the Array
LBU T0 18(S3) ; Chosen Player's Next Chain Space Index
SB T0 3(T1) ; Store in the Array
LBU T0 21(S3) ; Chosen Player's Previous Chain Index
SB T0 4(T1) ; Store in the Array
LBU T0 22(S3) ; Chosen Player's Previous Chain Space Index
SB T0 5(T1) ; Store in the Array

LBU A0 29(S4) ; Current Player's Index
LUI A1 hi(ChosenPlayerSpaces_Array)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(ChosenPlayerSpaces_Array)
JAL SetPlayerOntoChainVisually ; This sets the player visually and internally on the spaces
NOP

LBU A0 29(S3) ; Current Player's Index
LUI A1 hi(CurrentPlayerSpaces_Array)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(CurrentPlayerSpaces_Array)
JAL SetPlayerOntoChainVisually ; This sets the player visually and internally on the spaces
NOP

JAL PlaySound 
LI A0 0x107 ; Warp Block Sound Index

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 15 ; Frames

LI A0 1 ; Fade style (Circle)
JAL InitFade
LI A1 1 ; Fade type (In)

J goodbye
NOP

;==================================================SPACE SHUFFLE EVENT

spaceshuffle:
JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x2A0 ; Koopa Kid Bark sfx

LUI A1 hi(SpaceShuffle_Message)
JAL ShowMessage_Function ; Display and Close Message
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(SpaceShuffle_Message)

LI A0 1 ; Fade style (Circle)
JAL InitFade
LI A1 0 ; Fade type (out)

JAL PlaySound 
LI A0 0x107 ; Warp Block Sound Index

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 15 ; Frames

LUI S5 hi(Player1Spaces_Array)
ADDIU S5 S5 lo(Player1Spaces_Array)
LI S0 3 ; Start with Player 4
spaceshuffleloop:
BLTZ S0 spaceshuffleloop_exit ; exit once all player's positions are stored
NOP 
JAL GetPlayerStruct ; Struct at V0
MOVE A0 S0 ; Player Index

SLL T1 S0 0x0005 ; Multiply Player Index by 20 for alignment of Array
ADDU T1 T1 S5 ; Add to get the correct Array

LBU T0 15(V0) ; Player's Current Chain Index
SB T0 0(T1) ; Store in the Array
LBU T0 16(V0) ; Player's Current Chain Space Index
SB T0 1(T1) ; Store in the Array
LBU T0 17(V0) ; Player's Next Chain Index
SB T0 2(T1) ; Store in the Array
LBU T0 18(V0) ; Player's Next Chain Space Index
SB T0 3(T1) ; Store in the Array
LBU T0 21(V0) ; Player's Previous Chain Index
SB T0 4(T1) ; Store in the Array
LBU T0 22(V0) ; Player's Previous Chain Space Index
SB T0 5(T1) ; Store in the Array

J spaceshuffleloop
ADDIU S0 S0 -1 ; Subtract 1 to get the next player

spaceshuffleloop_exit:
LI S0 3 ; Start with Player 4
LI S7 0xF ; 1111 Flag for players whose position isn't taken yet
spaceshuffleloop2:
BLTZ S0 spaceshuffleloop2_exit ; exit once all players are affected
NOP
LI T0 1
BEQ S0 T0 spaceshuffleproblemcheck ; branch when it's Player 2's turn to check availability
NOP
spaceshufflerandomize:
JAL GetRandomByte ; 0-255 Number at V0
NOP
LI T0 4
DIVU V0 T0 ; Divide by 4 to get other player
MFHI V0 ; Remainder of division at V0 (0-3)
BEQ V0 S0 spaceshuffleloop2 ; If it's the current player, reroll
NOP
spaceshuffleskiprandomization:
LI T0 1
SLLV T0 T0 V0 ; Shift bit to the left by Player's Index
AND T2 T0 S7 ; T2 = 1 if the chosen player's location is available
BEQZ T2 spaceshuffleloop2 ; reroll if that player's location isn't available
NOP
SUBU S7 S7 T2 ; Turn flag off for that player's location
SLL A1 V0 0x0005 ; Multiply Player Index by 20 for alignment of Array

MOVE A0 S0 ; Player Index
JAL SetPlayerOntoChainVisually
ADDU A1 A1 S5 ; Add to get the correct Array

J spaceshuffleloop2
ADDIU S0 S0 -1 ; Subtract 1 to warp the next player

spaceshuffleproblemcheck:
ANDI T1 S7 1 ; T1 = 1 if Player 1's spot is available
BNEZL T1 spaceshuffleskiprandomization ; If it's available, branch and choose Player 1
LI V0 0 
J spaceshufflerandomize ; If not available, branch and randomize selection
NOP

spaceshuffleloop2_exit:
JAL PlaySound 
LI A0 0x107 ; Warp Block Sound Index

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 15 ; Frames

LI A0 1 ; Fade style (Circle)
JAL InitFade
LI A1 1 ; Fade type (In)

J goodbye
NOP

;===================================================ITEM SHUFFLE EVENT

itemshuffle:
JAL GetSumOfPlayerItems
NOP

BNEZ V0 itemshuffle2 ; If anything other than 0, continue
NOP

LI T0 EventIndex 
BEQZ T0 randomizeevent ; If the creator chose to randomize the event, pick a different one.
NOP
J noitemsforshuffle
NOP

itemshuffle2:
JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x2A0 ; Koopa Kid Bark sfx

LUI A1 hi(ItemShuffle_Message)
JAL ShowMessage_Function ; Display and Close Message
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(ItemShuffle_Message)

LUI S5 hi(ItemShuffle_Array)
ADDIU S5 S5 lo(ItemShuffle_Array)
LI S0 3 ; Start with Player 4
LI S3 0 ; Item Counter
itemshuffleloop:
BLTZ S0 itemshuffleloop_exit ; Exit once all player's items are gathered
NOP

JAL GetPlayerStruct ; Struct at V0
MOVE A0 S0 ; Player Index

LI T0 0xFF ; No item

LBU T2 24(V0) ; Item #1 Index
SB T0 24(V0) ; Delete Item
ADDU T1 S5 S3 ; Add Item Counter to get the right spot in the Array
SB T2 0(T1) ; Store in Array
ADDIU S3 S3 1 ; Add 1 to Item Counter

LBU T2 25(V0) ; Item #2 Index
SB T0 25(V0) ; Delete Item
ADDU T1 S5 S3 ; Add Item Counter to get the right spot in the Array
SB T2 0(T1) ; Store in Array
ADDIU S3 S3 1 ; Add 1 to Item Counter

LBU T2 26(V0) ; Item #3 Index
SB T0 26(V0) ; Delete Item
ADDU T1 S5 S3 ; Add Item Counter to get the right spot in the Array
SB T2 0(T1) ; Store in Array
ADDIU S3 S3 1 ; Add 1 to Item Counter

JAL RefreshHUD
MOVE A0 S0 ; Player Index

J itemshuffleloop
ADDIU S0 S0 -1 ; Subtract 1 to get next player 

itemshuffleloop_exit:
JAL PlaySound 
LI A0 0x367 ; Items Going in Sound Index
JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 30

JAL PlaySound 
LI A0 0x320 ; Items Shuffle Sound Index
JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 60 ; Frames


LI S7 0 ; bit flag for equal distribution
Mshuffleitemsloop2:
LI S6 0 ; Counter for no items left
LI T1 0xF ; All players given an item
BEQL S7 T1 Mshuffleitemsloop2
LI S7 0 ; Reset flag
JAL GetRandomByte ; 0-255 at V0
NOP 
LI T0 4 
DIVU V0 T0 ; Divide by 4
MFHI S0 ; Player's Index (0-3)

LI T1 1 
SLLV T2 T1 S0 ; Shift Left by Player Index 

AND V1 S7 T2 ; Compare Flag Value to Player Index
; V1 returns 0 if player has not been given an item, 1 if they have.
BNEZ V1 Mshuffleitemsloop2
NOP

MOVE T5 S5 ; Pass Array to T5
Mshuffleitemsloop3:
LI T1 12 
BEQ S6 T1 goodbye ; exit because there's no items left
NOP
LBU T3 0(T5) ; Load Item Index from Array
LI T1 0xFF ; No Item
ADDIU T5 T5 1 ; add to check next spot in the array
BEQL T3 T1 Mshuffleitemsloop3 ; 
ADDIU S6 S6 1 ; Add 1 to counter

Mshuffleitemsloop4:
JAL GetRandomByte ; 0-255 at V0
NOP 
LI T0 12
DIVU V0 T0 ; Divide by 12
MFHI T6 ; 12 Item spots (0-11)
ADDU T1 S5 T6 ; Add to get correct space in the Array
LBU S3 0(T1) ; Load Item Index from Array
LI T3 0xFF ; No Item Index
BEQ S3 T3 Mshuffleitemsloop4 ; loop if there's no item in that spot
NOP
SB T3 0(T1) ; Delete Item from the Array

JAL GetPlayerStruct ; at V0
MOVE A0 S0 ; Player Index

MOVE S6 V0 ; Copy Struct to S6

JAL PlayerHasEmptyItemSlot ; 0,1,2 at V0
MOVE A0 S0 ; Player Index

ADDIU S6 S6 24 ; Item #1 Address
ADDU S6 S6 V0 ; Add to get correct Item Slot Address
SB S3 0(S6) ; Give Item

JAL PlaySound
LI A0 25 ; Got Item Sound Index
JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 20 ; Frames

LI T1 1 
SLLV T2 T1 S0 ; Shift Left by Player Index 
J Mshuffleitemsloop2
ADDU S7 S7 T2 ; Mark the player as given an item




goodbye:
JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x2A0 ; Koopa Kid Bark sfx

LUI A1 hi(Goodbye_Message)
JAL ShowMessage_Function ; Display and Close Message
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(Goodbye_Message)
J exit
NOP

alreadycursed:
JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x2A0 ; Koopa Kid Bark sfx

LUI A1 hi(Cursed_Message)
JAL ShowMessage_Function ; Display and Close Message
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(Cursed_Message)

LUI A1 hi(AlreadyCursed_Message)
JAL ShowMessage_Function ; Display and Close Message
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(AlreadyCursed_Message)
J exit
NOP

nocoinsforrevolution:
JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x2A0 ; Koopa Kid Bark sfx

LUI A1 hi(Revolution_Message)
JAL ShowMessage_Function ; Display and Close Message
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(Revolution_Message)
J nocoins
NOP

nocoinsforswap:
JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x2A0 ; Koopa Kid Bark sfx

LUI A1 hi(CoinSwap_Message)
JAL ShowMessage_Function ; Display and Close Message
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(CoinSwap_Message)

nocoins:
LUI A1 hi(NoCoins_Message)
JAL ShowMessage_Function ; Display and Close Message
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(NoCoins_Message)
J exit
NOP

noitemsforshuffle:
JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x2A0 ; Koopa Kid Bark sfx

LUI A1 hi(ItemShuffle_Message)
JAL ShowMessage_Function ; Display and Close Message
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(ItemShuffle_Message)

SetPlayerOntoChainVisually:
ADDIU SP SP -80
SW RA 76(SP)
SW S0 72(SP) ; Array Pointer
SB A0 68(SP) ; Player's Index 

MOVE S0 A1 ; Copy Array Pointer to S0

LBU A0 68(SP) ; Player Index
LBU A1 0(S0) ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL SetPlayerOntoChain
LBU A2 1(S0) ; Assigns Space Index to A2

LBU A0 68(SP) ; Player Index
LBU A1 2(S0) ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL SetNextChainAndSpace
LBU A2 3(S0) ; Assigns Space Index to A2

LBU A0 68(SP) ; Player Index
LBU A1 4(S0) ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL SetPrevChainAndSpace
LBU A2 5(S0) ; Assigns Space Index to A2

LBU A0 0(S0) ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL GetAbsSpaceIndexFromChainSpaceIndex ; Gets True Space Index at V0
LBU A1 1(S0) ; Assigns Space Index to A2

JAL GetSpaceData ; Pointer to Space Data at V0
MOVE A0 V0 ; True Space Index

LW V1 8(V0) 
SW V1 64(SP) ; Store on the Stack

LW V1 16(V0)
SW V1 60(SP) ; Store on the Stack

JAL GetPlayerStruct ; Player Struct at V0
LBU A0 68(SP)  ; Player Index

LW V1 0x24(V0) ; Load Offset 0x24 into V1
ADDIU V1 V1 0xC ; Add 0xC to get current player's X Coords
LW T0 64(SP) ; Load Space X Coords from Stack
SW T0 0(V1) 

ADDIU V1 V1 8 ; This should load current player's Y Coords
LW T1 60(SP) ; Load Space Y Coords from Stack
SW T1 0(V1)

LW S0 72(SP) ; Array Pointer
LW RA 76(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 80

.align 16
GetSumOfPlayerItems:
ADDIU SP SP -80
SW RA 76(SP)
SW S0 72(SP)
SW S1 68(SP)

LI S0 3 ; Start with Player 4
LI S1 0 ; Item Counter
GetSumOfPlayerItems_loop:
BLTZ S0 GetSumOfPlayerItems_exit
NOP

JAL PlayerHasEmptyItemSlot ; Empty Item Slot Index at V0 (0, 1, 2, -1)
MOVE A0 S0 ; Player Index

LI T0 -1 ; No Inventory Index
BLTZL V0 GetSumOfPlayerItems_add
LI V0 3 ; If no space, make it 3 items

GetSumOfPlayerItems_add:
ADDU S1 S1 V0 ; Add to the Item Counter
J GetSumOfPlayerItems_loop
ADDIU S0 S0 -1 ; Subtract 1 to get next player


GetSumOfPlayerItems_exit:
MOVE V0 S1 ; Move Item Counter to proper register
LW S1 68(SP)
LW S0 72(SP)
LW RA 76(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 80

;=================================================================INFO

; To change the sound indexes for Playsound, use the PartyPlanner
; audio section to find the sound index you want, then use the
; following link to match the correct Playsound index (left number):
; https://pastebin.com/H1jxNFqr

; If you want to know how to change the character portrait on the
; message box, use the following link:
; https://github.com/PartyPlanner64/PartyPlanner64/wiki/Displaying-Messages

; If you want to know how to put special characters on your message
; or know what they mean, use the following link:
; https://github.com/PartyPlanner64/PartyPlanner64/wiki/String-Encoding
;
; Previously, special characters were put on messages as ".byte" with
; the special character index right after, but we've found that you 
; can actually put the special characters in the ascii by using \x
; So what used to be ".byte 0xC2" for an exclamation mark, can now
; be written as \xC2 to save an entire line of code\xC2 (get it?)

1/5 Turns Event (Bank Rule Added After T.code:
; NAME: 1/5 Turns Event (Bank Rule Added After Turn)
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct

;====================================================================
; Made by Spongyoshi, feel free to use for your own boards
; Put it as an "After Turn" event on your board
; Activates on Last 5 Turns and offers something to last place
; If picked "Get Item" you get a random item
; If picked "Get Coins" you start an event related to currency
; If picked "Something Else..." a new rule gets added
; If multiple people are last, they all get an item
; Thanks to Airsola, Rain & Justin from the MPL Discord!
;====================================================================

ADDIU SP SP -80
SW RA 76(SP)
SW S1 72(SP) ;holds total turn number
SW S2 68(SP) ;holds various values for testing
SW S3 64(SP) ;holds various values & addresses
SW S4 60(SP) ;holds various values & loops
SW S5 56(SP) ;holds current player index address
SW S6 52(SP) ;holds current turn number
SW S0 48(SP) ;holds various values for testing

LUI S5 hi(current_player_index)
ADDIU S5 S5 lo(current_player_index) ; Loading current player address

LUI T1 hi(current_turn)
ADDIU T1 T1 lo(current_turn) ; Loading address of current turn number
LBU T1 0(T1) ; Loading current turn number
LUI T0 hi(total_turns)
ADDIU T0 T0 lo(total_turns) ; Loading address of total turn number
LBU T0 0(T0) ; Loading total turn number

; Newly added code to only activate Turn 2/10, 3/15, 4/20, etc.
LI T2 5
DIVU T0 T2
MFLO T3
BEQ T1 T3 P1IsLast
NOP
J exit
NOP

LI A0 11 ; Generic Fade-out

LI A0 11 ; Generic Fade-in

JAL SleepProcess

;Now start the window

NOP

SW R0 24(SP)

SW T0 28(SP)
LUI A1 hi(Boost_Message)

JAL 0x800EC6C8

LI A0 11 ; Generic Fade-in

;==========find 4th place==========
start:
LI S2 1 ;give the info that it's the last 5 turns
LUI S3 hi(0x800CD0A1)
ADDIU S3 S3 lo(0x800CD0A1) ; Loading board ram address
SB S2 0(S3)

LI A0 11 ; Generic Fade-out 
JAL InitFadeOut
LI A1 5 ; Fade Out for 5 Frames

JAL SleepProcess
ADDIU A0 R0 10

JAL PlayMusic
LI A0 19 ;Play the last 5 turns music

LI S2 3 ;Get 4th place

JAL GetPlayerPlacement
LI A0 0
BEQ V0 S2 P1IsLast ; If P1's placement is 4th, they are last
NOP

JAL GetPlayerPlacement
LI A0 1
BEQ V0 S2 P2IsLast ; If P2's placement is 4th, they are last
NOP

JAL GetPlayerPlacement
LI A0 2
BEQ V0 S2 P3IsLast ; If P3's placement is 4th, they are last
NOP

JAL GetPlayerPlacement
LI A0 3
BEQ V0 S2 P4IsLast ; If P4's placement is 4th, they are last
NOP
;==========find 4th place end==========

;==========find 3rd place==========
;Else, search for third place
LI S6 0 ;emptied S6
LI S2 2 ;Get 3th place

JAL GetPlayerPlacement
LI A0 0
BEQ V0 S2 P1IsThird ; If P1's placement is 3th, they are last
NOP
KeepSearch1:
JAL GetPlayerPlacement
LI A0 1
BEQ V0 S2 P2IsThird ; If P2's placement is 3th, they are last
NOP
KeepSearch2:
JAL GetPlayerPlacement
LI A0 2
BEQ V0 S2 P3IsThird ; If P3's placement is 3th, they are last
NOP
KeepSearch3:
JAL GetPlayerPlacement
LI A0 3
BEQ V0 S2 P4IsThird ; If P4's placement is 3th, they are last
NOP
;==========find 3rd place end==========

;==========find 2nd place==========
;Else, search for second place
LI S3 0 ;emptied S3
LI S2 1 ;Get 2th place

JAL GetPlayerPlacement
LI A0 0
BEQ V0 S2 P1IsSecond ; If P1's placement is 2th, they are last
NOP
KeepSearch4:
JAL GetPlayerPlacement
LI A0 1
BEQ V0 S2 P2IsSecond ; If P2's placement is 2th, they are last
NOP
KeepSearch5:
JAL GetPlayerPlacement
LI A0 2
BEQ V0 S2 P3IsSecond ; If P3's placement is 2th, they are last
NOP
KeepSearch6:
JAL GetPlayerPlacement
LI A0 3
BEQ V0 S2 P4IsSecond ; If P4's placement is 2th, they are last
NOP

J exitwindow ;if not, everyone is first, event is cancelled
NOP
;==========find 2nd place end==========

;==========ALL the tests==========
P1IsLast:
JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x11 ; Mushroom Growth Sound
LI S2 0 ;Get Player 1
SB S2 0(S5) ;Send it as the current player index
J choicewindow ;Start the Last 5 Turns Event
NOP
P2IsLast:
LI S2 1 ;Get Player 2
SB S2 0(S5) ;Send it as the current player index
J choicewindow ;Start the Last 5 Turns Event
NOP
P3IsLast:
LI S2 2 ;Get Player 3
SB S2 0(S5) ;Send it as the current player index
J choicewindow ;Start the Last 5 Turns Event
NOP
P4IsLast:
LI S2 3 ;Get Player 3
SB S2 0(S5) ;Send it as the current player index
J choicewindow ;Start the Last 5 Turns Event
NOP

P1IsThird:
LI S6 1 ;Get Player 1
J KeepSearch1 ;Find the second
NOP
P2IsThird:
BEQ R0 S6 altKeepSearch2 ; Check if S6 is empty

choicewindow:

LI A1 5 ; Fade Out for 5 Frames

LI S3 6 ;preventive action for the loop
LI S6 6 ;preventive action for the loop
; Greetings window
JAL GetCurrentPlayerCharacterString
NOP
SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
ADDI A0 R0 0x3 ; Character image (Toad)
LUI A1 hi(promptMessage)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(promptMessage)
MOVE A2 V0 ; Pass Character Name to A2
JAL ShowMessage
LI A3 0

; Get the selection, either from the player or CPU.
; If A0 is a pointer to AI data, AI logic is ran to pick for CPUs.
; If A0 is 0 or 1, the 0th or 1st option is chosen by CPUs.
; If A0 is 2, then the value of A1 is the CPUs option index choice.
LI A0 0
JAL GetBasicPromptSelection
LI A1 0
MOVE S0 V0 ; S0 now has the chosen option index

; Obligatory message box closing/cleanup calls.
JAL CloseMessage
NOP
jal   0x800EC9DC
       NOP
jal   0x800EC6EC
       NOP

; Change the outcome based on the choice.
LI A0 0
BEQ S0 A0 SomeRules
NOP
LI A0 1
BEQ S0 A0 SomeRules
NOP
LI A0 2
BEQ S0 A0 SomeRules
NOP

;==========2P Giveaway Window==========
TwoPlayerGiveaway:
LI A0 11 ; Generic Fade-in
JAL InitFadeIn
LI A1 5 ; Fade Out for 5 Frames

SW R0 16(SP)
SW R0 20(SP)
SW R0 24(SP)
LI T0 0x64 ; 100 Units Y pos
SW T0 28(SP)
ADDI A0 R0 0x3 ; Character image (Toad)
LUI A1 hi(Item_Giveaway_Message)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(Item_Giveaway_Message)
LI A2 0
JAL 0x800EC980 ; ShowMessage2 
LI A3 0
JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP

LI S4 0 ;Initialize the value of the loop
LI S3 6 ;preventive action for the loop
;==========2P Giveaway Window END==========

;==========2P Giveaway Character Select==========
2PLoopBack:
LI A0 11 ; Generic Fade-out 
JAL InitFadeOut
LI A1 5 ; Fade Out for 5 Frames

JAL SleepProcess
ADDIU A0 R0 7

LI A0 11 ; Generic Fade-in
JAL InitFadeIn
LI A1 5 ; Fade Out for 5 Frames

ADDIU S4, S4, 1 ;Add 1 to S4
LI S0 1 ;See if it's the first loop
BEQ S0, S4, 2PLoopingBack ;If so, branch out
NOP
LI S0 3 ;If not, See if it's the last loop
BEQ S0, S4, exiteventwindow ;If so, end of giveaway
NOP
LI S0 1
SUBU S0, S6, S0 ; Substract one to get the exact index
SB S0 0(S5);if not, give first player to current player index
J Continue2PGive
NOP

2PLoopingBack:
LI S0 1
SUBU S0, S1, S0 ; Substract one to get the exact index
SB S0 0(S5);if so, give second player to current player index
J Continue2PGive
NOP
;==========2P Giveaway Character Select END==========

;==========2P Giveaway Selection==========
Continue2PGive:
LI S1 0 ;emptied S1
JAL GetRandomByte ; Random Int at V0
NOP

SLTI S0 V0 80 ; Is the number less than 80?
BNE S0 R0 DuelGloveGiveaway2P
NOP

SLTI S0 V0 160 ; Is the number less than 160?
BNE S0 R0 GoldenMushroomGiveaway2P
NOP

SLTI S0 V0 240 ; Is the number less than 240?
BNE S0 R0 CellularShopperGiveaway2P
NOP

J MagicLampGiveaway2P
NOP
;==========2P Giveaway Selection END==========

;==========2P Giveaway Window Selection==========
DuelGloveGiveaway2P: ;Giving away Duel Glove
ADDIU S1 R0 0x08 ; Dueling Glove value
LUI A1 hi(Duel_Glove_Get)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(Duel_Glove_Get)
J GiveWindow
NOP
GoldenMushroomGiveaway2P: ;Giving away Golden Mushroom
ADDIU S1 R0 0x0A ; Golden Mushroom value
LUI A1 hi(Gold_Shroom_Get)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(Gold_Shroom_Get)
J GiveWindow
NOP
CellularShopperGiveaway2P: ;Giving away Cellular Shopper
ADDIU S1 R0 0x04 ; Cellular Shopper value
LUI A1 hi(Toad_Phone_Get)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(Toad_Phone_Get)
J GiveWindow
NOP

LUI A1 hi(Magic_Lamp_Get)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(Magic_Lamp_Get)
J GiveWindow
NOP

; BEGIN DETERMINE PLAYER CODE
determineplayer:
JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex
NOP

ADDU S0 R0 R0

LUI S2 hi(p1_item1)
ADDIU S2 S2 lo(p1_item1)

BEQ S0 V0 determineslot
NOP
ADDIU S0 S0 1

LUI S2 hi(p2_item1)
ADDIU S2 S2 lo(p2_item1)

BEQ S0 V0 determineslot
NOP
ADDIU S0 S0 1

LUI S2 hi(p3_item1)
ADDIU S2 S2 lo(p3_item1)

BEQ S0 V0 determineslot
NOP
ADDIU S0 S0 1

LUI S2 hi(p4_item1)
ADDIU S2 S2 lo(p4_item1)
; END DETERMINE PLAYER CODE

; BEGIN ANALYZE INVENTORY CODE
determineslot:
ADDIU S0 R0 0xFF
LBU V0 0(S2)
BEQ S0 V0 giveitem ; First slot is empty (0xFF)
NOP
ADDIU S2 S2 1
LBU V0 0(S2)
BEQ S0 V0 giveitem ; Second slot is empty
NOP
ADDIU S2 S2 1
LBU V0 0(S2)
BEQ S0 V0 giveitem ; Third slot is empty
NOP
; END ANALYZE INVENTORY CODE

; BEGIN SHOW "CANNOT GIVE ITEM" MESSAGE CODE
promptdisplay:
SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
LI A0 -1 ; Character image (None)
LUI A1 hi(DeleteItem)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(DeleteItem)
ADDU A2 R0 R0
JAL 0x800EC8EC ; ShowMessage
ADDU A3 R0 R0

; Get the selection, either from the player or CPU.
; If A0 is a pointer to AI data, AI logic is ran to pick for CPUs.
; If A0 is 0 or 1, the 0th or 1st option is chosen by CPUs.
; If A0 is 2, then the value of A1 is the CPUs option index choice.
LI A0 0
JAL GetBasicPromptSelection
LI A1 0
MOVE S0 V0 ; S0 now has the chosen option index

; Obligatory message box closing/cleanup calls.
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP

; Change the player's destination based on the choice.
LI A0 0
BEQ S0 A0 DelItem1
NOP
LI A0 1
BEQ S0 A0 DelItem2
NOP
LI A0 2
BEQ S0 A0 DelItem3
NOP
LI A0 3
BEQ S0 A0 finish_giveaway
NOP
; END SHOW "CANNOT GIVE ITEM" MESSAGE CODE

;HAPPY CODE
HappyCode:
JAL GetPlayerStruct
LI A0 -1
LBU T0 3(V0)
JAL PlaySound
ADDIU A0 T0 0x275 ; Add Mario's Happy Voice Index
JAL GetHappyPlayer
NOP
J Sound
NOP
;HAPPY CODE

;DelItems & giveitem
DelItem1:
LI S0 0x2
SUBU S2 S2 S0
SB S1 0(S2)
J HappyCode
NOP

DelItem2:
LI S0 0x1
SUBU S2 S2 S0
SB S1 0(S2)
J HappyCode
NOP

DelItem3:
SB S1 0(S2)
J HappyCode
NOP

giveitem:
SB S1 0(S2)
J HappyCode
NOP

Sound:
ADDIU A0 R0 0x10C ; turn start sound
JAL PlaySound
NOP

ADDIU A0 R0 15
JAL SleepProcess ; Sleeps for 15 frames
NOP
;DelItems & giveitem END

;==========End of Giveaway Window==========
finish_giveaway:
SLTI S0 S3 5 ; Is S3 less than 5?
BNE S0 R0 3PLoopBack ;if so, go back to 3P Giveaway loop
NOP

SLTI S0 S6 5 ; Else, Is S6 less than 5?
BNE S0 R0 2PLoopBack ;if so, go back to 2P Giveaway loop
NOP
;else, end the event
;==========End of Giveaway Window end==========

;==========End of Event Window==========
exiteventwindow:
SW R0 16(SP)
SW R0 20(SP)
SW R0 24(SP)
LI T0 0x64 ; 100 Units Y pos
SW T0 28(SP)
ADDI A0 R0 0x3 ; Character image (Toad)
LUI A1 hi(EndingEvent_Message)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(EndingEvent_Message)
LI A2 0
JAL 0x800EC980 ; ShowMessage2 
LI A3 0
JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP

LI A0 11 ; Generic Fade-out 
JAL InitFadeOut
LI A1 5 ; Fade Out for 5 Frames
JAL SleepProcess
ADDIU A0 R0 10 ;Sleep for 8 frames
LI A0 11 ; Generic Fade-in
JAL InitFadeIn
LI A1 5 ; Fade Out for 5 Frames

J exit
NOP
;==========End of Event Window end==========

NOP

NOP

exit:
LI S2 3
SB S2 0 (S5) ;giving back player 4 to current player index
;and end
LW RA 76(SP)
LW S1 72(SP)
LW S2 68(SP)
LW S3 64(SP)
LW S4 60(SP)
LW S5 56(SP)
LW S6 52(SP)
LW S0 48(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 80

; NAME: TRGTRG Multiple Choice [16Q 4Ans FIRST SET]

; PARAM: +Number|IncorrectAnswer

;====================================================================
; IMPORTANT: This code is specifically designed to make a quiz for
;            player. If the player answers correctly, they win Coins.
;            If they get it wrong, they lose Coins. There are 8
;            questions total from which the game picks 1 at random.
;===================================================================

ADDIU SP SP -60
SW RA 56(SP)
SW S0 52(SP)
SW S5 48(SP)
SW S4 44(SP)
SW S3 40(SP)
SW S2 36(SP)

FinishPrompt:
ADDU A2 R0 R0
JAL 0x800EC8EC ; ShowMessage
ADDU A3 R0 R0

; If A0 is a pointer to AI data, AI logic is ran to pick for CPUs.
; If A0 is 0 or 1, the 0th or 1st option is chosen by CPUs.
; If A0 is 2, then the value of A1 is the CPUs option index choice.
J AILogic
NOP
AISelect:
LI A0 2
JAL GetBasicPromptSelection
MOVE A1 S5 ; A1 now has the AI's decision
MOVE S0 V0 ; S0 now has the chosen option index

; Obligatory message box closing/cleanup calls.
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP
;END FINALIZING PROMPT QUESTION======================================

JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x3EC ; Drumroll

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 25

JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x3ED ; Drumroll end

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 25

; Change the result based on the choice.
BEQ S0 S4 correct
NOP
J incorrect
NOP

TRGTRG Multiple Choice [16Q 4Ans SECOND.code:
; NAME: TRGTRG Multiple Choice [16Q 4Ans SECOND SET]
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct
; PARAM: +Number|CorrectAnswer
; PARAM: +Number|IncorrectAnswer

;====================================================================
; IMPORTANT: This code is specifically designed to make a quiz for
;            player. If the player answers correctly, they win Coins.
;            If they get it wrong, they lose Coins. There are 8
;            questions total from which the game picks 1 at random.
;===================================================================

ADDIU SP SP -60
SW RA 56(SP)
SW S0 52(SP)
SW S5 48(SP)
SW S4 44(SP)
SW S3 40(SP)
SW S2 36(SP)
SW S1 32(SP)



JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x4FD ; Lucky 7 Step Sound

JAL PlayMusic
LI A0 46 ; Don't Hurry

;BEGIN INTRODUCTION MESSAGE==========================================
SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
LI A0 -1 ; Character image (-1 for none)
LUI A1 hi(Introduction)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(Introduction)
LI A2 0x0
JAL 0x800EC8EC ; ShowMessage
LI A3 0x0

JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP
;END INTRODUCTION MESSAGE============================================

JAL GetRandomByte ; Random Int at V0
NOP

;BEGIN PREPARING BEGINNING OF PROMPT=================================
SW R0 20(SP) ; A4
SW R0 24(SP) ; A5
SW R0 28(SP) ; A6
LI A0 -1 ; Character image (None)
;END PREPARING BEGINNING OF PROMPT===================================

;BEGIN CHOOSING PROMPT QUESTION======================================
LI T0 16
SLT S0 V0 T0 ; Is the number less than 16?
NOP
BNE S0 R0 Question1
NOP

NOP

NOP

FinishPrompt:
ADDU A2 R0 R0
JAL 0x800EC8EC ; ShowMessage
ADDU A3 R0 R0

; If A0 is a pointer to AI data, AI logic is ran to pick for CPUs.
; If A0 is 0 or 1, the 0th or 1st option is chosen by CPUs.
; If A0 is 2, then the value of A1 is the CPUs option index choice.
J AILogic
NOP
AISelect:
LI A0 2
JAL GetBasicPromptSelection
MOVE A1 S5 ; A1 now has the AI's decision
MOVE S0 V0 ; S0 now has the chosen option index

; Obligatory message box closing/cleanup calls.
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP
;END FINALIZING PROMPT QUESTION======================================

JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x3EC ; Drumroll

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 25

JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x3ED ; Drumroll end

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 25

; Change the result based on the choice.
BEQ S0 S4 correct
NOP
J incorrect
NOP

;BEGIN CORRECT ANSWER PATH===========================================
correct:
JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x419 ; Fanfare (Curtain Call)

;BEGIN CONGRATULATORY MESSAGE========================================
LUI A0 hi(coin_string_loc)
ADDIU A0 A0 lo(coin_string_loc)
LUI A1 hi(percent_d)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(percent_d)
JAL sprintf
LI A2 CorrectAnswer

SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
LI A0 -1 ; Character image (-1 for none)
LUI A1 hi(Congratulations_Message)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(Congratulations_Message)
LUI A2 hi(coin_string_loc)
ADDIU A2 A2 lo(coin_string_loc)
JAL 0x800EC8EC ; ShowMessage
LI A3 0x0

JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP
;END CONGRATULATORY MESSAGE==========================================

JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex ; Index at V0
NOP

MOVE S4 V0 ; Move Index to S4
LUI S1 hi(p1_char)
ADDIU S1 S1 lo(p1_char) ; Load Player 1's Character address
LI S3 0x38 ; Distance between each player's Character address
MULT S4 S3 ;  Multiply Current Player Index by S3
MFLO S3 ; Move the result to S3

ADDU S1 S1 S3 ; Add result to get current Player's Star address
LBU S2 0(S1) ; Load address value into S2

JAL PlaySound
ADDIU A0 S2 0x2BE ; Mario's Taunt Index

MOVE A0 S4 ; Presumably needs current player's index
LI A1 5 ; Joy Animation
JAL 0x800F2304 ; CueAnimation
LI A2 0

MOVE A0 S4
JAL AdjustPlayerCoinsGradual
LI A1 CorrectAnswer

MOVE A0 S4
JAL ShowPlayerCoinChange
LI A1 CorrectAnswer

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 30

JAL GetBoardAudioIndex
NOP

JAL PlayMusic
MOVE A0 V0

J exit
NOP
;END CORRECT ANSWER PATH=============================================

AILogic:
JAL GetRandomByte ; at V0
NOP

LI T0 0x40
SLT S0 V0 T0 ; Is the number less than 64?
NOP
BNE S0 R0 Choose1st
NOP

LI T0 0x80
SLT S0 V0 T0 ; Is the number less than 128?
NOP
BNE S0 R0 Choose2nd
NOP

LI T0 0xC0
SLT S0 V0 T0 ; Is the number less than 192?
NOP
BNE S0 R0 Choose3rd
NOP

J Choose4th
NOP

Choose1st:
LI S5 0
J AISelect
NOP

Choose2nd:
LI S5 1
J AISelect
NOP

Choose3rd:
LI S5 2
J AISelect
NOP

Choose4th:
LI S5 3
J AISelect
NOP

TRGTRG Star Spot Active (4/5 Turns).code:
; NAME: TRGTRG Star Spot Active (4/5 Turns)
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct
; PARAM: +Number|Price



;====================================================================
; IMPORTANT: This code is specifically designed to allow the landing
;            or passing player to purchase a Star at a cost of your
;            choice. It includes the "Star Get" jingle and dance
;            animation for your character. Make sure you change the
;            music track it plays near the end of the code to match
;            the one selected for your board.
;===================================================================



addiu SP, SP, -0x60
sw    RA, 0x34(SP)
SW S4 24(SP)
SW S1 40(SP)
SW S2 36(SP)
SW S3 28(SP)
SW S0 32(SP)

LUI T1 hi(current_turn)
ADDIU T1 T1 lo(current_turn) ; Loading address of current turn number
LBU T1 0(T1) ; Loading current turn number
LUI T0 hi(total_turns)
ADDIU T0 T0 lo(total_turns) ; Loading address of total turn number
LBU T0 0(T0) ; Loading total turn number

; Newly added code to hopefully only activate after 8/10 turns
LI T2 5 ;            Load 5 into T2
DIVU T0 T2 ;         Divide T0 by T2
MFLO T3 ;            Store Result in T3
LI T2 4 ;            Load 4 into T2
MULT T3 T2 ;         Multiply T3 by T2
MFLO T4 ;            Store Result in T4
SUB T5 T4 T1 ;       Subtract T4 by T1, store result in T2
BGEZ T5 exit ;       If T5 is greater or equal to 0, exit
NOP

;BEING CHECKING PLAYER FOR NECESSARY COINS============================
JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex ; Current Player Index at V0
NOP

MOVE S4 V0 ; Copied Current Player Index to S4
MOVE A0 S4 ; Copied Current Player Index to A0
LI A1 Price ; Amount of coins to check for
JAL PlayerHasCoins ; Checks if Player has A1's amount of Coins
NOP

BEQ V0 R0 NotEnoughCoins ; If insufficient funds, branch
NOP
;END CHECKING PLAYER FOR NECESSARY COINS==============================

;BEGIN CHECKING IF PLAYER CAN CARRY A STAR============================
LUI S1 hi(p1_stars)
ADDIU S1 S1 lo(p1_stars) ; Load Player 1's Star address
LI S3 0x38 ; This is the distance between each player's Star address
MULT S4 S3 ;  Multiply Current Player Index by S3
MFLO S3 ; Move the result to S3

ADDU S1 S1 S3 ; Add result to get current Player's Star address
LBU S2 0(S1) ; Load address value into S2

LI T0 0x63 ; 99
BEQ S2 T0 TooManyStars ; If the player has 99 Stars, exit
NOP
;END CHECKING IF PLAYER CAN CARRY A STAR==============================

;BEGIN LOADING STRING VALUES FOR PROMPT===============================
LUI S0 hi(p1_char)
ADDIU S0 S0 lo(p1_char) ; Load Player 1's Character address
ADDU S0 S0 S3 ; Add result from above to S0
LBU S2 0(S0) ; Load the value address value of S0 into S2

LI T0 0x1c00 ; Load value of MARIO string to T0
ADDU S2 S2 T0 ; Add S2 to the string value to obtain the character

LUI A0 hi(coin_string_loc)
ADDIU A0 A0 lo(coin_string_loc) ; Parse Destination
LUI A1 hi(percent_d)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(percent_d) ; String Format

LI A2 Price ; Convert Price into string
;END LOADING STRING VALUES FOR PROMPT=================================

;BEGIN PROMPT=========================================================
START:
SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
LI A0 3 ; Character image (Toad)
LUI A1 hi(promptMessage)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(promptMessage)
MOVE A2 S2 ; Pass Character Name to A2
LUI A3 hi(coin_string_loc)
ADDIU A3 A3 lo(coin_string_loc) ; Pass Star Price to A3
JAL 0x800EC8EC ; ShowMessage
NOP

; Get the selection, either from the player or CPU.
; If A0 is a pointer to AI data, AI logic is ran to pick for CPUs.
; If A0 is 0 or 1, the 0th or 1st option is chosen by CPUs.
; If A0 is 2, then the value of A1 is the CPUs option index choice.
LI A0 2
JAL GetBasicPromptSelection
LI A1 0 ; CPU will always say yes
MOVE S0 V0 ; S0 now has the chosen option index

; Obligatory message box closing/cleanup calls.
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP

; Change the outcome based on the choice.
LI A0 0
BEQ S0 A0 yes
NOP
LI A0 1
BEQ S0 A0 Declined
NOP
LI A0 2
BEQ S0 A0 view_map
NOP
;END PROMPT===========================================================

yes:

MOVE A0 S4 ; Current Player's Index moved to A0
SUBU A1 R0 S0 ; Amount to pay
JAL AdjustPlayerCoinsGradual ; Changes Player's coin amount
NOP

MOVE A0 S4 ; Current Player's Index moved to A0
SUBU A1 R0 S0 ; Amount to display
JAL ShowPlayerCoinChange ; Displays Player's coin loss on-screen 
NOP

ADDIU A0 R0 35
JAL SleepProcess ; Sleeps for 35 frames
NOP

TRGTRG SetSpaceType (Seamless 3/5 Turns).code:
; NAME: TRGTRG SetSpaceType (Seamless 3/5 Turns)
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct
; PARAM: Space|space0
; PARAM: Space|space1
; PARAM: Space|space2
; PARAM: Space|space3
; PARAM: Space|space4
; PARAM: Space|space5
; PARAM: Space|space6
; PARAM: Space|space7

LUI T1 hi(current_turn)
ADDIU T1 T1 lo(current_turn) ; Loading address of current turn number
LBU T1 0(T1) ; Loading current turn number
LUI T0 hi(total_turns)
ADDIU T0 T0 lo(total_turns) ; Loading address of total turn number
LBU T0 0(T0) ; Loading total turn number

; Newly added code to hopefully only activate after 6/10 turns
LI T2 5 ;            Load 5 into T2
DIVU T0 T2 ;         Divide T0 by T2
MFLO T3 ;            Store Result in T3
LI T2 3 ;            Load 4 into T2
MULT T3 T2 ;         Multiply T3 by T2
MFLO T4 ;            Store Result in T4
SUB T5 T4 T1 ;       Subtract T4 by T1, store result in T2
BGEZ T5 Function2 ;       If T5 is greater or equal to 0, exit
NOP

//0x800FD55C hook here
insertHook:
LUI t0, 0x8010
LUI t1, hi(jumpCustomCodeLabel)
LW t1, lo(jumpCustomCodeLabel) (t1)
SW t1, 0xD55C (t0) //store hook to our code
SW r0, 0xD560 (t0) //store nop after hook insertion
JR RA
NOP

jumpCustomCodeLabel:
J customCode

//add custom spaces here, make sure 0 terminates the list
.align 0x10
activeSpaces:
.byte space0
.byte space1
.byte space2
.byte space3
.byte space4
.byte space5
.byte space6
.byte space7
.byte 0 //0 terminate list

.align 0x10
customCode:
LUI at, 0x800D //restore instruction
SW v0, 0x41C0 (at) //restore instruction
BNEZ v0, exitCustom
NOP
ADDIU sp, sp, -0x20
SW ra, 0x0014 (sp)
SW s0, 0x0018 (sp)
SW s1, 0x001C (sp)
//get random value
JAL getSpaceTypeFromRand
NOP
ADDU s0, v0, r0 //move random value to s0

//get current player space
JAL GetPlayerStruct
ADDIU a0, r0, 0xFFFF

//get space abs
LB a0, 0x000F (v0) //load current player chain index
JAL GetAbsSpaceIndexFromChainSpaceIndex
LB a1, 0x0010 (v0) //load current player space index
ADDU s1, v0, r0 //space index moved to s1


JAL checkForActiveSpaces
ADDU a0, s1, r0 //space index moved to a0

ADDIU v1, r0, 0xFFFF
BEQ v0, v1, spaceNotFound
NOP

ADDU a0, s1, r0
JAL SetSpaceType
ADDU a1, s0, r0 //space type to set

spaceNotFound:
LW ra, 0x0014 (sp)
LW s0, 0x0018 (sp)
LW s1, 0x001C (sp)
ADDIU sp, sp, 0x20
exitCustom:
J 0x800FD564 //jump back to after hook
NOP

getSpaceTypeFromRand:
ADDIU sp, sp, -0x20
SW ra, 0x0018 (sp)
JAL GetRand
ORI a0, r0, 69 //0-69 returned
SLTI t0, v0, 10 //0-9
BNEL t0, r0, spaceTypeRandEnd
ORI v0, r0, 1 //blue space
SLTI t0, v0, 20 //10-19
BNEL t0, r0, spaceTypeRandEnd
ORI v0, r0, 2 //red space
SLTI t0, v0, 30 //20-29
BNEL t0, r0, spaceTypeRandEnd
ORI v0, r0, 5 //chance time space
SLTI t0, v0, 40 //30-39
BNEL t0, r0, spaceTypeRandEnd
ORI v0, r0, 6 //item space
SLTI t0, v0, 50 //40-49
BNEL t0, r0, spaceTypeRandEnd
ORI v0, r0, 9 //battle minigame space
SLTI t0, v0, 60 //50-59
BNEL t0, r0, spaceTypeRandEnd
ORI v0, r0, 12 //bowser space
//60-69
ORI v0, r0, 15 //game guy
spaceTypeRandEnd:
LW ra, 0x0018 (sp)
JR RA
ADDIU sp, sp, 0x20

checkForActiveSpaces:
LI t0, activeSpaces
activeSpacesLoop:
LB t1, 0x0000 (t0)
BEQZ t1, endOfList
NOP
BEQ t1, a0, spaceFound
NOP
BEQ r0, r0, activeSpacesLoop
ADDIU t0, t0, 1

endOfList:
BEQ r0, r0, endOfActiveSpaces
ADDIU v0, r0, 0xFFFF //return -1
spaceFound:
ADDU v0, a0, r0 //return space type found
endOfActiveSpaces:
JR RA
NOP

//custom get rand implementation from paper mario, updated
//to use mp3 lcg
.align 0x10
GetRand:
ADDIU sp, sp, -0x18
SW ra, 0x0010 (sp)
BLTZL a0, label1_func0
SUBU a0, r0, a0
label1_func0:
BEQZ a0, End1
DADDU v0, r0, r0
ADDIU v0, r0, 0x0001
BNEL a0, v0, label2_func0
ADDIU v0, r0, 0x0064
JAL Function1
ADDIU a0, r0, 0x03E8
SLTI v0, v0, 0x01F5
J End1
XORI v0, v0, 0x0001
label2_func0:
BEQ a0, v0, label3_func0
NOP
JAL Function1
NOP
J End1
NOP
label3_func0:
JAL Function1
ADDIU a0, r0, 0x03F1
LUI v1, 0x6666
ORI v1, v1, 0x6667
MULT v0, v1
SRA v0, v0, 31
MFHI a1
SRA v1, a1, 2
SUBU v0, v1, v0
End1:
LW ra, 0x0010 (sp)
JR RA
ADDIU sp, sp, 0x18
;
Function1:
ADDIU sp, sp, -0x20
SW s0, 0x0010 (sp)
ADDIU s0, r0, 0xFFFF
SW s1, 0x0014 (sp)
ADDIU s1, a0, 0x0001
BNEZ s1, label1_func1
DIVU s0, s1
BREAK 0x01C00
label1_func1:
MFLO s0
BNEZ s0, label2_func1 ;800299C4
SW ra, 0x0018 (sp)
ADDIU s0, r0, 0x0001
label2_func1:
JAL Function2 ;80029900
NOP
BNEZ s0, label3_func1 ;800299D8
DIVU v0, s0
BREAK 0x01C00
label3_func1:
MFLO v1
SLTU v0, v1, s1
BEQZ v0, label2_func1 ;800299C4
DADDU v0, v1, r0
LW ra, 0x0018 (sp)
LW s1, 0x0014 (sp)
LW s0, 0x0010 (sp)
JR RA
ADDIU sp, sp, 0x20
;
Function2:
LUI v0, 0x8009
LW v0, 0x7650 (v0)
LUI v1, 0x41C6
ORI v1, v1, 0x4E6D
MULT v0, v1
MFLO v0
ADDIU v0, v0, 0x3039
LUI v1, 0x8009
JR RA
SW v0, 0x7650 (v1)

; A0 = Current Player's Index
ADDIU SP SP -32
SW RA 28(SP)

LI T2 0x38 ; Distance between each player's addresses

LBU T2 0(T0) ; Load the value address value of S0 into S2

TRGTRG Prediction of Jeanie (Before Dice.code:
; NAME: TRGTRG Prediction of Jeanie (Before Dice Roll)
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct
; PARAM: Space|SpaceDirection

ADDIU SP SP -80
SW RA 76(SP)
SW S1 72(SP) ;holds plant number
SW S2 68(SP) ;used to store various values
SW S3 64(SP) ;holds the RAM address 1 of CW
SW S4 60(SP) ;used for warp & curse values
SW S5 56(SP) ;holds the value of the RAM address 1 of CW
SW S6 52(SP) ;used for the Nipper event
SW S0 48(SP) ;used to store various values

LUI T1 hi(current_turn)
ADDIU T1 T1 lo(current_turn) ; Loading address of current turn number
LBU T1 0(T1) ; Loading current turn number
LUI T0 hi(total_turns)
ADDIU T0 T0 lo(total_turns) ; Loading address of total turn number
LBU T0 0(T0) ; Loading total turn number

; Newly added code to hopefully only activate this every 6 turns
LI T2 6
DIVU T1 T2
MFHI T3
BNEZ T3 exit
NOP

;===Set Player Idle Animation===
LI A0 -1 ; Load Current Player Index
LI A1 -1 ; Set player's idle animation
JAL SetBoardPlayerAnimation
LI A2 2 ; Loop the animation

;===Rotate Player Model Towards Space===
LI A0 -1 ; Load Current Player Index
LI A1 10 ; Frames it takes to turn
JAL 0x800ED20C ; RotatePlayerModel function
LI A2 SpaceDirection ; Space Index to face towards

;FIRST WINDOW===============================================
JAL PlaySound ; Play Sparkles Sound
LI A0 0x11B

JAL SleepProcess ; Sleeps for 40 frames
ADDIU A0 R0 40

SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
LI A0 0x3C ; Character image (Jeanie)
LUI A1 hi(Prediction_Start)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(Prediction_Start)

ADDU A2 R0 R0
JAL 0x800EC8EC ; ShowMessage
ADDU A3 R0 R0

JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP

JAL PlaySound ; Play Magic Power Sound
LI A0 0x11A

JAL SleepProcess ; Sleeps for 20 frames
ADDIU A0 R0 20
;FIRST WINDOW END===========================================

;SELECTION OF WINDOW===========================================
JAL GetRandomByte ; Random Int at V0
NOP

SLTI S0 V0 80 ; Is the number less than 80?
BNE S0 R0 HappeningTest
NOP

SLTI S0 V0 160 ; Is the number less than 160?
BNE S0 R0 CoinTest
NOP

SLTI S0 V0 240 ; Is the number less than 240?
BNE S0 R0 GameTest
NOP

J LeadingTest
NOP
;END SELECTION OF WINDOW=======================================

;REST OF THE WINDOW===================================================
RestWindow:
SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
LI A0 0x3C ; Character image (Jeanie)
LI A2 0
JAL ShowMessage
LI A3 0

JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP

JAL SleepProcess ; Sleeps for 15 frames
ADDIU A0 R0 15

J exit
NOP
;REST OF THE WINDOW END===============================================

;CHECKS FOR BONUS STARS===========================================
;HAPPENING STAR
HappeningTest:
JAL GetCurrentPlayerHappeningStarCount
LI S2 0x2;
ADDU S1 S2 V0 ; Add S2 to the value

LUI S2 hi(p1_happening_space_count)
ADDIU S2 S2 lo(p1_happening_space_count) ; Loading P1 ?STAR
LBU S2 0(S2)

SLT S0 S1 S2; Is P1 Happening Star higher than current player?
NOP
BNE S0 R0 NormalWindow 
NOP

LUI S2 hi(p2_happening_space_count)
ADDIU S2 S2 lo(p2_happening_space_count) ; Loading P2 ?STAR
LBU S2 0(S2)

SLT S0 S1 S2; Is P2 Happening Star higher than current player?
NOP
BNE S0 R0 NormalWindow
NOP

LUI S2 hi(p3_happening_space_count)
ADDIU S2 S2 lo(p3_happening_space_count) ; Loading P3 ?STAR
LBU S2 0(S2)

SLT S0 S1 S2; Is P3 Happening Star higher than current player?
NOP
BNE S0 R0 NormalWindow
NOP

LUI S2 hi(p4_happening_space_count)
ADDIU S2 S2 lo(p4_happening_space_count) ; Loading P4 ?STAR
LBU S2 0(S2)

SLT S0 S1 S2; Is P4 Happening Star higher than current player?
NOP
BNE S0 R0 NormalWindow
NOP

J HappeningWindow
NOP
;COIN STAR
CoinTest:
JAL GetCurrentPlayerCoinStarCount
LUI S2 hi(bank_coin_total)
ADDIU S2 S2 lo(bank_coin_total) ; Loading coins in bank in S2
LHU S2 0(S2)
ADDU S1 S2 V0 ; Add S2 to the value

LUI S2 hi(p1_coin_star)
ADDIU S2 S2 lo(p1_coin_star) ; Loading P1 $STAR
LHU S2 0(S2)

SLT S0 S1 S2; Is P1 Coin Star higher than current player?
NOP
BNE S0 R0 NormalWindow
NOP

LUI S2 hi(p2_coin_star)
ADDIU S2 S2 lo(p2_coin_star) ; Loading P2 $STAR
LHU S2 0(S2)

SLT S0 S1 S2; Is P2 Coin Star higher than current player?
NOP
BNE S0 R0 NormalWindow
NOP

LUI S2 hi(p3_coin_star)
ADDIU S2 S2 lo(p3_coin_star) ; Loading P3 $STAR
LHU S2 0(S2)

SLT S0 S1 S2; Is P3 Coin Star higher than current player?
NOP
BNE S0 R0 NormalWindow
NOP

LUI S2 hi(p4_coin_star)
ADDIU S2 S2 lo(p4_coin_star) ; Loading P4 $STAR
LHU S2 0(S2)

SLT S0 S1 S2; Is P4 Coin Star higher than current player?
NOP
BNE S0 R0 NormalWindow
NOP

J CoinWindow
NOP
;GAME STAR
GameTest:
JAL GetCurrentPlayerMiniGameStarCount
LUI S2 hi(current_turn)
ADDIU S2 S2 lo(current_turn) ; Loading current turn number in S2
LBU S2 0(S2)
ADDU S1 S2 V0 ; Add S2 to the value

LUI S2 hi(p1_minigame_star)
ADDIU S2 S2 lo(p1_minigame_star) ; Loading P1 GSTAR
LHU S2 0(S2)

SLT S0 S1 S2; Is P1 MiniGame Star higher than current player?
NOP
BNE S0 R0 NormalWindow
NOP

LUI S2 hi(p2_minigame_star)
ADDIU S2 S2 lo(p2_minigame_star) ; Loading P2 GSTAR
LHU S2 0(S2)

SLT S0 S1 S2; Is P2 MiniGame Star higher than current player?
NOP
BNE S0 R0 NormalWindow
NOP

LUI S2 hi(p3_minigame_star)
ADDIU S2 S2 lo(p3_minigame_star) ; Loading P3 GSTAR
LHU S2 0(S2)

SLT S0 S1 S2; Is P3 MiniGame Star higher than current player?
NOP
BNE S0 R0 NormalWindow
NOP

LUI S2 hi(p4_minigame_star)
ADDIU S2 S2 lo(p4_minigame_star) ; Loading P4 GSTAR
LHU S2 0(S2)

SLT S0 S1 S2; Is P4 MiniGame Star higher than current player?
NOP
BNE S0 R0 NormalWindow
NOP

J GameWindow
NOP
;LEADER TEST
LeadingTest:
JAL GetCurrentPlayerStarCount
NOP
MOVE S2 V0 ; S2 = V0
JAL GetFirstPlaceStarCount
NOP
BEQ S2 V0 LeadingRandom ;Does current player have the same number of stars as first place?
NOP
J NormalWindow
NOP
;LEADER RANDOM
LeadingRandom:
JAL GetRandomByte ; Random Int at V0
NOP

SLTI S0 V0 80 ; Is the number less than 80?
BNE S0 R0 HappeningWindow
NOP

SLTI S0 V0 160 ; Is the number less than 160?
BNE S0 R0 CoinWindow
NOP

SLTI S0 V0 240 ; Is the number less than 240?
BNE S0 R0 GameWindow
NOP

J NormalWindow
NOP
;CHECKS FOR BONUS STARS END=======================================

;ALL THE WINDOWS===============================================
HappeningWindow:
LUI A1 hi(Prediction_Happening)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(Prediction_Happening)
;Implement text of the window
J RestWindow
NOP
GameWindow:
LUI A1 hi(Prediction_Minigame)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(Prediction_Minigame)
;Implement text of the window
J RestWindow
NOP

Tumble Time (Before Dice Roll).code:
; NAME: Tumble Time (Before Dice Roll)
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct

ADDIU SP SP -88
SW RA 80(SP)
SW S0 76(SP)
SW S1 64(SP)
SW S3 60(SP)
SW S4 56(SP)
SW S5 52(SP)
SW S6 48(SP)
SW S7 44(SP)

; S1 = Multiplier for Bonus
; S3 = Current Player's Index
; S4 = 4
; S5 = Coins for Bonus/Giveaway
; S6 = Current Turn Tier
; S7 = Current Turn Tier + Current Player's Placing (0-11)

JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex ; Current Player Index at V0
NOP
MOVE S3 V0 ; Move Current Player's Index to S3


LI S4 4

LUI T1 hi(current_turn)
ADDIU T1 T1 lo(current_turn) ; Loading address of current turn number
LBU T1 0(T1) ; Loading current turn number
LUI T0 hi(total_turns)
ADDIU T0 T0 lo(total_turns) ; Loading address of total turn number
LBU T0 0(T0) ; Loading total turn number

; Newly added code to hopefully only activate this every 3 turns
LI T2 3
DIVU T1 T2
MFHI T3
BNEZ T3 exit
NOP

LI S7 0 ; Early Game Value on S7
LI A2 0x6
SLT S0 T1 A2
NOP
BNE S0 R0 Continue1 ; If it's less than 6, then it's Early Game, exit
NOP
LI S7 8 ; Late Game Value on S7
SUB A2 T0 T1
LI T0 0x5
SLT S0 A2 T0
NOP
BNE S0 R0 Continue1 ; If it's 4 or less, it's Lategame, exit
NOP
LI S7 4 ; Mid Game Value on S7

Continue1:
MOVE S6 S7 ; S6 now contains Turn Tier

JAL GetPlayerPlacement ; Current Player Placing at V0
MOVE A0 S3

ADDU S7 S7 V0 ; Placing + Turn Tier at S7

JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x2A8 ; Tumble: Hi

SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
LI A0 0x15 ; Character image (Tumble)
LUI A1 hi(TumbleGreeting)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(TumbleGreeting)
LI A2 0
JAL 0x800EC8EC ; ShowMessage
LI A3 0

JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP

; S7 = Placing + Turn Tier
BEQ S6 R0 RollEarly
NOP
BEQ S7 S4 RollMid1st
NOP
LI T0 7
SLT S0 S7 T0
NOP
BNE S0 R0 RollMid23
NOP
BEQ S7 T0 RollMid4th
NOP
LI T0 8
BEQ S7 T0 RollLate1st
NOP
LI T0 9
BEQ S7 T0 RollLate2nd
NOP
LI T0 10
BEQ S7 T0 RollLate3rd
NOP
J RollLate4th
NOP

Calculate:
LI S0 0 ; Start with Player 1
LOOP:
LI T0 10 ; T0 holds value of MAX_COINS
LI T1 5 ; T1 holds value of MIN_COINS
ADDIU T0 T0 1 
SUBU S5 T0 T1 ; S1 = Max Coins - Min Coins 
JAL GetRandomByte ; Generates a number from 0-255 into V0
NOP
DIVU V0 S5 ; Divide the random number by the number of outcomes
MFHI S5 ; HI contains the remainder, pull that into S1
ADDIU S5 S5 5 ; Add MIN_COINS
MULT S1 S5 ; Multiply the Coins by the Multiplier
MFLO S5 ; Move Value to S5

MOVE A0 S0 ; Assigns Current Player's Index to A0
JAL AdjustPlayerCoinsGradual ; Changes player's coin amount
MOVE A1 S5 ; Move amount of Coins to A1

ContinueLoop:
LI A0 -1 ; Current Player
LI A1 5 ; Jumping Joy Animation Index
JAL SetBoardPlayerAnimation
LI A2 0 ; Don't repeat animation

MOVE A0 S3
JAL gethappyvoice
NOP

LI T0 3
BEQ S0 T0 ExitLoop ; If it's done with Player 4, exit loop
NOP

ADDIU S0 S0 1
J LOOP
NOP

JAL SleepProcess 
LI A0 35 ; Sleeps for 35 frames

J exit
NOP

AdjustPlayerStars:
ADDIU SP SP -32
SW RA 28(SP)

LUI T1 hi(p1_stars)

LI T0 0x38 ; Distance between each player's Star address

MFLO T0 ; Move the result to S3

ADDU T1 T1 T0 ; Add result to get current Player's Star address
LBU T0 0(T1) ; Load address value into S2

SB T0 0(T1)

JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 32

TRGTRG Golden Mushroomizer Guaranteed (B.code:
; NAME: TRGTRG Golden Mushroomizer Guaranteed (Before Player Turn)
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct
; PARAM: Number|Odds

ADDIU SP SP -40
SW RA 0(SP)
SW S1 4(SP)
SW S2 8(SP)

LUI T1 hi(current_turn)
ADDIU T1 T1 lo(current_turn) ; Loading address of current turn number
LBU T1 0(T1) ; Loading current turn number
LUI T0 hi(total_turns)
ADDIU T0 T0 lo(total_turns) ; Loading address of total turn number
LBU T0 0(T0) ; Loading total turn number

; Newly added code to hopefully only activate this every 10 turns
LI T2 10
DIVU T1 T2
MFHI T3
BNEZ T3 exit
NOP

JAL RNGPercentChance
LI A0 Odds

BNE V0 R0 hit
NOP
J exit
NOP
hit:

LI A0 1 ;Current player
LI A1 3 ;3 for Golden, 2 for Mushroom
JAL 0x800DE9AC

exit:
LW S1 4(SP)
LW S2 8(SP)
LW RA 0(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 40

TRGTRG Mushroomizer Guaranteed with Mess.code:
; NAME: TRGTRG Mushroomizer Guaranteed with Message (Before Player Turn)
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct
; PARAM: Number|Odds

ADDIU SP SP -40
SW RA 0(SP)
SW S1 4(SP)
SW S2 8(SP)

LUI T1 hi(current_turn)
ADDIU T1 T1 lo(current_turn) ; Loading address of current turn number
LBU T1 0(T1) ; Loading current turn number
LUI T0 hi(total_turns)
ADDIU T0 T0 lo(total_turns) ; Loading address of total turn number
LBU T0 0(T0) ; Loading total turn number

; Newly added code to hopefully only activate this every 5 turns
LI T2 5
DIVU T1 T2
MFHI T3
BNEZ T3 exit
NOP

JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x11 ; Mushroom Growth Sound

SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
ADDI A0 R0 -1 ; Character image (-1 for none)
LUI A1 hi(message)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(message)
ADDU A2 R0 R0
JAL 0x800EC8EC ; ShowMessage
ADDU A3 R0 R0

; The rest here perform the "wait for confirmation"
; and probably messagebox teardown.
JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP

JAL RNGPercentChance
LI A0 Odds

BNE V0 R0 hit
NOP
J exit
NOP
hit:

LI A0 1 ;Current player
LI A1 2 ;3 for Golden, 2 for Mushroom
JAL 0x800DE9AC

exit:
LW S1 4(SP)
LW S2 8(SP)
LW RA 0(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 40

.align 16
message:
.byte 0x0B ; Start the message
.ascii "Every five turns"
.byte 0x82 ;
.ascii " a"
.byte 0x0A ; Newline
.byte 0x03 ; 
.ascii "Mushroomizer"
.byte 0x08 ; White font
.ascii " will power"
.byte 0x0A ; Newline
.ascii "up your next dice roll"
.byte 0xC2 ;
.byte 0xFF,0 ; FF=Pause

TRGTRG Online Shopping.code:
; NAME: TRGTRG Online Shopping
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct
; PARAM: +Number|PriceTier1
; PARAM: +Number|PriceTier2
; PARAM: +Number|PriceTier3
; PARAM: +Number|PriceTier4
; PARAM: +Number|PriceTier5

ADDIU SP SP -72
SW RA 64(SP)
SW S1 60(SP)
SW S2 56(SP)
SW S7 52(SP)
SW S3 48(SP)
SW S4 44(SP)
SW S5 40(SP)
SW S6 36(SP)

JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x18 ; 1-up Sound

; S1 holds current player item address
; S4 current player index
; S2 total turns value
; S3 current turn value
; S5 item received
; S6 Price Tier
; S7 Got Item Message

LI A0 -1 ; Current Player
LI A1 -1 ; Idle Animation Index
JAL SetBoardPlayerAnimation
LI A2 2 ; Loop Animation

;FAILSAFE CHECKS START===============================================
LUI T1 hi(total_turns)
ADDIU T1 T1 lo(total_turns) ; Load address of Total Turns to T1
LBU S2 0(T1) ; Load value of Total Turns to S2

LUI T0 hi(current_turn)
ADDIU T0 T0 lo(current_turn) ; Load address of Current Turn to T0
LBU S3 0(T0) ; Load value of Current Turn to S3

BEQ S2 S3 LastTurn ; If it's the last turn, branch
NOP

JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex ; Current Player's Index at V0
NOP
MOVE S4 V0 ; Copy Current Player Index to S4

LUI S1 hi(p1_item3)
ADDIU S1 S1 lo(p1_item3) ; Load Player 1's Item slot #3 address
LI T0 0x38 ; This is the distance between each player's Item #3
MULT S4 T0 ;  Multiply Current Player Index by S3
MFLO T0 ; Move the result to S3

ADDU S1 S1 T0 ; Add result to get current Player's item slot #3
LBU T1 0(S1) ; Load address value into S2

LI T0 0xFF ; No Item Value
BNE T1 T0 TooManyItems ; If the player's inventory is full, exit
NOP

MOVE A0 S4
JAL PlayerHasCoins ; Returns 0 if FALSE
LI A1 PriceTier1

BEQ V0 R0 NotEnoughCoins
NOP
;FAILSAFE CHECKS END=================================================

START:
SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
LI A0 0x27 ; Character image (Cellular Shopper)
LUI A1 hi(ItemMachine_Prompt)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(ItemMachine_Prompt)
LI A2 0
LI A3 0
JAL 0x800EC8EC ; ShowMessage
NOP

; If A0 is a pointer to AI data, AI logic is ran to pick for CPUs.
; If A0 is 0 or 1, the 0th or 1st option is chosen by CPUs.
; If A0 is 2, then the value of A1 is the CPUs option index choice.
J AIChoice
NOP
AISelection:
LI A0 2
JAL GetBasicPromptSelection
MOVE A1 V0
MOVE S0 V0 ; S0 now has the chosen option index

; Obligatory message box closing/cleanup calls.
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP

; Change the outcome based on the choice.
LI A0 0
BEQ S0 A0 yes
NOP
LI A0 1
BEQ S0 A0 exit
NOP
LI A0 2
BEQ S0 A0 viewmap
NOP

yes:
LI A0 0 ; Assigns Bar Code fade-out
JAL InitFadeOut ; Fade to black
LI A1 16 ; Assigns 16 frames of fade-out

JAL SleepProcess ; Sleeps for 26 frames
LI A0 26

JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x3F9 ; Item Drop Sound

JAL SleepProcess ; Sleeps for 10 frames
LI A0 10

LI A0 0 ; Assigns Bar Code fade-in
JAL InitFadeIn ; Fade in
LI A1 16 ; Assigns 16 frames of fade-in

JAL SleepProcess ; Sleeps for 16 frames
LI A0 16

ITEMROLL:
JAL GetRandomByte ; Random Int at V0
NOP
; S2 total turns value
; S3 current turn value
SLTI S0 S3 6
NOP
BNE S0 R0 EarlyGame ; If it's less than 6, then it's Early Game
NOP
SUB T1 S2 S3
SLTI S0 T1 5
NOP
BNE S0 R0 LateGame ; If it's less than 4, it's Late Game
NOP
J MidGame ; Otherwise, it's Mid Game
NOP

TRGTRG Item Shop.code:
; NAME: TRGTRG Item Shop
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct
; PARAM: +Number|MinToShop
; PARAM: +Number|SkeletonKeyPrice
; PARAM: +Number|MushroomPrice
; PARAM: +Number|ReverseMushroomPrice
; PARAM: +Number|GoldenMushroomPrice
; PARAM: +Number|KoopaKardPrice
; PARAM: +Number|MagicLampPrice
; PARAM: +Number|ItemBagPrice

;====================================================================
; IMPORTANT: This code is specifically designed to allow the landing
;            or passing player to purchase an item from an inventory
;            of your choice. If the player's inventory is full, they
;            don't get to buy anything.
;===================================================================

ADDIU SP SP -40
SW RA 36(SP)
SW S1 32(SP)
SW S2 28(SP)
SW S0 24(SP)
SW S3 20(SP)
SW S4 16(SP)
SW S5 8(SP)


;BEGIN Checks that prevent purchase===================================
LUI S1 hi(total_turns)
ADDIU S1 S1 lo(total_turns) ; Load address of Total Turns to S1
LBU S1 0(S1) ; Load value of Total Turns to S1

LUI S2 hi(current_turn)
ADDIU S2 S2 lo(current_turn) ; Load address of Current Turn to S2
LBU S2 0(S2) ; Load value of Current Turn to S2

BEQ S2 S1 LastTurn ; If it's the last turn, branch
NOP

JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex ; Current Player's Index at V0
NOP

MOVE S4 V0 ; Copy Current Player Index to S4
MOVE A0 S4 ; Copy Current Player Index to A0
LI A1 MinToShop ; A1 = The minimum amount of Coins to shop
JAL PlayerHasCoins ; Checks if Player has the minimum Coins 
NOP

BEQ V0 R0 NoCoinsToShop ; If the player doesn't have the Coins, exit
NOP

LUI S1 hi(p1_item3)
ADDIU S1 S1 lo(p1_item3) ; Load Player 1's Item slot #3 address
LI S3 0x38 ; This is the distance between each player's Item #3
MULT S4 S3 ;  Multiply Current Player Index by S3
MFLO S3 ; Move the result to S3

ADDU S1 S1 S3 ; Add result to get current Player's item slot #3
LBU S2 0(S1) ; Load address value into S2

LI T0 0xFF ; No Item Value
BNE S2 T0 TooManyItems ; If the player's inventory is full, exit
NOP
;END Checks that prevent purchase=====================================

;BEGIN GREETING=======================================================
JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x298 ; Toad: Yahoo! ^_^/

SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
ADDI A0 R0 0x3 ; Character image (Toad)
LUI A1 hi(Greeting_Message)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(Greeting_Message)
ADDU A2 R0 R0
JAL 0x800EC8EC ; ShowMessage
ADDU A3 R0 R0

JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP
;END GREETING=========================================================

;BEGIN ITEM SELECTION PROMPT==========================================
START:
SW R0 20(SP) ; A4
SW R0 24(SP) ; A5
SW R0 28(SP) ; A6
LI A0 0x3 ; Character image (Toad)
LUI A1 hi(ItemSelection_Prompt)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(ItemSelection_Prompt)
ADDU A2 R0 R0
JAL 0x800EC8EC ; ShowMessage
ADDU A3 R0 R0

; Get the selection, either from the player or CPU.
; If A0 is a pointer to AI data, AI logic is ran to pick for CPUs.
; If A0 is 0 or 1, the 0th or 1st option is chosen by CPUs.
; If A0 is 2, then the value of A1 is the CPUs option index choice.
LI A0 0
JAL GetBasicPromptSelection
LI A1 0 ; A1 now has the AI's decision
MOVE S0 V0 ; S0 now has the chosen option index

; Obligatory message box closing/cleanup calls.
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP

; Change the player's destination based on the choice.
LI A0 0
BEQ S0 A0 item1
NOP
LI A0 1
BEQ S0 A0 item2
NOP
LI A0 2
BEQ S0 A0 item3
NOP
LI A0 3
BEQ S0 A0 item4
NOP
LI A0 4
BEQ S0 A0 item5
NOP
LI A0 5
BEQ S0 A0 item6
NOP
LI A0 6
BEQ S0 A0 itembag
NOP
LI A0 7
BEQ S0 A0 exit
NOP
LI A0 8
BEQ S0 A0 view_map
NOP
;END ITEM SELECTION PROMPT============================================

;BEGIN Item Values====================================================
; 0x00 = Mushroom
; 0x01 = Skeleton Key
; 0x02 = Poison Mushroom
; 0x03 = Reverse Mushroom
; 0x04 = Cellular Shopper
; 0x05 = Warp Block
; 0x06 = Plunder Chest
; 0x07 = Bowser Phone
; 0x08 = Dueling Glove
; 0x09 = Lucky Lamp
; 0x0A = Golden Mushroom
; 0x0B = Boo Bell
; 0x0C = Boo Repellant
; 0x0D = Bowser Suit
; 0x0E = Magic Lamp
; 0x0F = Koopa Card
; 0x10 = Barter Box
; 0x11 = Lucky Coin
; 0x12 = Wacky Watch
;END Item Values======================================================

;BEGIN Selected Option================================================
item1:
LI S0 0x1 ; Key Value
LI S3 SkeletonKeyPrice ; S3 contains Key Price
J payprice
NOP
item2:
LI S0 0x0 ; Mushroom Value
LI S3 MushroomPrice ; S3 contains Mushroom Price
J payprice
NOP
item3:
LI S0 0x3 ; Reverse Mushroom Value
LI S3 ReverseMushroomPrice ; S3 contains Reverse Mushroom Price
J payprice
NOP
item4:
LI S0 0xA ; Golden Mushroom Value
LI S3 GoldenMushroomPrice ; S3 contains Golden Mushroom Price
J payprice
NOP
item5:
LI S0 0xF ; Koopa Kard Value
LI S3 KoopaKardPrice ; S3 contains Koopa Kard Price
J payprice
NOP
item6:
LI S0 0xE ; Magic Lamp Value
LI S3 MagicLampPrice ; S3 contains Magic Lamp Price
J payprice
NOP
itembag:
LI S3 ItemBagPrice ; S3 contains Item Bag Price
MOVE A0 S4 ; Current Player's Index moved to A0
MOVE A1 S3 ; Amount of coins to check
JAL PlayerHasCoins ; Checks if Player has A1's amount of Coins
NOP

BEQ V0 R0 NotEnoughCoins ; If insufficient funds, branch
NOP

MOVE A0 S4 ; Current Player's Index moved to A0
SUBU A1 R0 S3 ; Amount to pay
JAL AdjustPlayerCoinsGradual ; Changes Player's coin amount
NOP

MOVE A0 S4 ; Current Player's Index moved to A0
SUBU A1 R0 S3 ; Amount to display
JAL ShowPlayerCoinChange ; Displays Player's coin loss on-screen 
NOP

ADDIU A0 R0 30
JAL SleepProcess ; Sleeps for 30 frames
NOP

LI T1 2 
SUBU S1 S1 T1 ; This loads the current player's first Item address
LI S5 1 ; S5 is the counter to stop giving Items once full
Loop:
LI T0 0x4
SLT A2 S5 T0 ; A2 = 1 if S5 is less than 4
NOP
BEQ A2 R0 exit ; exit once player's item inventory is full
NOP

LBU S2 0(S1) ; Load slot #1's Item Value into S2
LI T1 0xFF ; No Item Value
BNE S2 T1 next ; If the player has an item, load next address
NOP

JAL GetRandomByte ; Integer at V0
NOP

LI A0 0x6 
SLT S0 V0 A0 ; S0 = 1 if the number is less than 6
NOP
BNE S0 R0 getKoopaKard ; Branch if true
NOP

LI A0 0xF 
SLT S0 V0 A0 ; S0 = 1 if the number is less than 15
NOP
BNE S0 R0 getLuckyCharm ; Branch if true
NOP

LI A0 0x21 
SLT S0 V0 A0 ; S0 = 1 if the number is less than 33
NOP
BNE S0 R0 getBowserPhone ; Branch if true
NOP

LI A0 0x33
SLT S0 V0 A0 ; S0 = 1 if the number is less than 51
NOP
BNE S0 R0 getBowserSuit ; Branch if true
NOP

LI A0 0x45
SLT S0 V0 A0 ; S0 = 1 if the number is less than 69
NOP
BNE S0 R0 getLuckyLamp ; Branch if true
NOP

LI A0 0x74
SLT S0 V0 A0 ; S0 = 1 if the number is less than 116
NOP
BNE S0 R0 getWarpBlock ; Branch if true
NOP

LI A0 0xA3
SLT S0 V0 A0 ; S0 = 1 if the number is less than 163
NOP
BNE S0 R0 getPoisonMushroom ; Branch if true
NOP

LI A0 0xD2
SLT S0 V0 A0 ; S0 = 1 if the number is less than 210
NOP
BNE S0 R0 getMushroom ; Branch if true
NOP

J getSkeletonKey
NOP

getKoopaKard:
LI T0 0xF ; Koopa Kard value
SB T0 0(S1)
J sound
NOP

getLuckyCharm:
LI T0 0x11 ; Lucky Charm value
SB T0 0(S1)
J sound
NOP

getBowserPhone:
LI T0 0x7 ; Bowser Phone value
SB T0 0(S1)
J sound
NOP

getBowserSuit:
LI T0 0xD ; Bowser Suit value
SB T0 0(S1)
J sound
NOP

getLuckyLamp:
LI T0 0x9 ; Lucky Lamp value
SB T0 0(S1)
J sound
NOP

getWarpBlock:
LI T0 0x5 ; Warp Block value
SB T0 0(S1)
J sound
NOP

getPoisonMushroom:
LI T0 0x2 ; Poison Mushroom value
SB T0 0(S1)
J sound
NOP

getMushroom:
LI T0 0x0 ; Mushroom value
SB T0 0(S1)
J sound
NOP

getSkeletonKey:
LI T0 0x1 ; Skeleton Key value
SB T0 0(S1)

sound:
JAL PlaySound
ADDIU A0 R0 0x10C ; Turn Start sound

ADDIU A0 R0 30
JAL SleepProcess ; Sleeps for 30 frames
NOP

next:
ADDIU S1 S1 1 ; Load next item's address
ADDIU S5 S5 1 ; Raise the item counter by 1
J Loop ; Loop back to give the next item
NOP

view_map:
JAL ViewBoardMap
NOP
J START
NOP
;END Item Values======================================================

;BEGIN Checking Player For Necessary Coins To Purchase================
payprice:
MOVE A0 S4 ; Current Player's Index moved to A0
MOVE A1 S3 ; Amount of coins to check
JAL PlayerHasCoins ; Checks if Player has A1's amount of Coins
NOP

BEQ V0 R0 NotEnoughCoins ; If insufficient funds, branch
NOP
;END Checking Player For Necessary Coins To Purchase==================

;BEGIN Taking Coins From Player=======================================
MOVE A0 S4 ; Current Player's Index moved to A0
SUBU A1 R0 S3 ; Amount to pay
JAL AdjustPlayerCoinsGradual ; Changes Player's coin amount
NOP

MOVE A0 S4 ; Current Player's Index moved to A0
SUBU A1 R0 S3 ; Amount to display
JAL ShowPlayerCoinChange ; Displays Player's coin loss on-screen 
NOP

ADDIU A0 R0 30
JAL SleepProcess ; Sleeps for 30 frames
NOP
;END Taking Coins From Player=========================================

;BEGIN Checking Player Item Slots=====================================
LI T1 2
SUBU S1 S1 T1 ; This loads the current player's first Item address
LBU S2 0(S1) ; Load slot #1's Item Value into S2
LI T1 0xFF ; No Item Value
BEQ S2 T1 giveitem ; Go to giveitem if the slot is empty
NOP
ADDIU S1 S1 1 ; Add 1 to load current player's second Item address
LBU S2 0(S1) ; Load slot #2's Item Value into S2
BEQ S2 T1 giveitem ; Go to giveitem if the slot is empty
NOP
ADDIU S1 S1 1 ; Add 1 to load current player's third Item address

giveitem:
SB S0 0(S1)
;END Checking Player Item Slots=======================================

;BEGIN Item Sound Effect==============================================
JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x10C ; Turn Start sound

LI A0 15 ; Frames to wait after the sound plays
JAL SleepProcess ; Sleeps for 15 frames
NOP

J exit
NOP
;END Item Sound Effect================================================

;BEGIN CANNOT BUY ITEM MESSAGE========================================
NotEnoughCoins:
JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x29A ; Toad: Oooh :(

SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
ADDI A0 R0 0x3 ; Character image (Toad)
LUI A1 hi(NotEnoughCoins_Message)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(NotEnoughCoins_Message)
ADDU A2 R0 R0
JAL 0x800EC8EC ; ShowMessage
ADDU A3 R0 R0

JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP

J START
NOP
;END CANNOT BUY ITEM MESSAGE==========================================

;BEGIN TOO MANY ITEMS MESSAGE=========================================
TooManyItems:
JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x29A ; Toad: Oooh :(

SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
ADDI A0 R0 0x3 ; Character image (Toad)
LUI A1 hi(TooManyItems_Message)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(TooManyItems_Message)

J FinalizeMessage
NOP
;END TOO MANY ITEMS MESSAGE===========================================

;BEGIN NOT ENOUGH COINS MESSAGE=======================================
NoCoinsToShop:
JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x29A ; Toad: Oooh :(

SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
ADDI A0 R0 0x3 ; Character image (Toad)
LUI A1 hi(NoCoinsToShop_Message)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(NoCoinsToShop_Message)

J FinalizeMessage
NOP
;END NOT ENOUGH COINS MESSAGE=========================================

;BEGIN Last Turn MESSAGE==============================================
LastTurn:
JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x29A ; Toad: Oooh :(

SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
ADDI A0 R0 0x3 ; Character image (Toad)
LUI A1 hi(LastTurn_Message)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(LastTurn_Message)
;END Last Turn MESSAGE================================================

FinalizeMessage:
ADDU A2 R0 R0
JAL 0x800EC8EC ; ShowMessage
ADDU A3 R0 R0

JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP



exit:
LW S5 8(SP)
LW S4 16(SP)
LW S3 20(SP)
LW S1 32(SP)

Random Confirmation Message [Loserville].code:
; NAME: Random Confirmation Message [Loserville] FINAL_VERSION
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct

main:
; This code block generates a random 8-bit integer (0-255) and
; iteratively checks how big it is. Depending on its size, one of
; five different messages can be show. By changing the size and 
; number of the intervals, any number of items can be included in the 
; list with separate and specific odds of getting them.
ADDIU sp, sp, -0x30
SW ra, 0x001C (sp)
JAL getMessagePtr
NOP
SW r0, 0x0010 (sp) ; A4
SW r0, 0x0014 (sp) ; A5
SW r0, 0x0018 (sp) ; A6
ADDIU a0, r0, 0xFFFF ; Character image (-1 for none)
ADDU a1, v0, r0 //move message ptr to a1
ADDU A2 R0 R0
JAL ShowMessage ;0x800EC8EC
ADDU A3 R0 R0
NOP
JAL closeMessageWrapper
NOP
LW ra, 0x001C (sp)
JR RA
ADDIU sp, sp, 0x30


closeMessageWrapper:
ADDIU sp, sp, -0x20
SW ra, 0x0018 (sp)
JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL CloseMessage
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP
LW ra, 0x0018 (sp)
JR RA
ADDIU sp, sp, 0x20


getMessagePtr:
ADDIU sp, sp, -0x30
SW ra, 0x0018 (sp)
SW s0, 0x001C (sp)
SW s1, 0x0020 (sp)
SW s2, 0x0024 (sp)
SW s3, 0x0028 (sp)
//
JAL GetRandomByte
NOP
ADDU s0, v0, r0 //move random int to s0
ORI s1, r0, 0000 //loop counter
LUI s2, hi(messageBoxChances)
ADDIU s2, s2, lo(messageBoxChances)
LUI s3, hi(messageTextPtrs)
ADDIU s3, s3, lo(messageTextPtrs)
messagePtrLoop:
LH t0, 0x0000 (s2)
SLTU t0, t0, s0 //if random value is less than or equal to boxChances
BEQZ t0, exitMessagePtr
NOP
ADDIU s2, s2, 0x0002 //increment messageBoxChances ptr
BEQ r0, r0, messagePtrLoop
ADDIU s1, s1, 0x0001 //increment loop count
exitMessagePtr:
SLL v0, s1, 0002 //multiply by 4
ADDU v0, v0, s3 //add messageTextPtr + (0x04 * result)
LW v0, 0x0000 (v0) //load message pointer
//
LW ra, 0x0018 (sp)
LW s0, 0x001C (sp)
LW s1, 0x0020 (sp)
LW s2, 0x0024 (sp)
LW s3, 0x0028 (sp)
JR RA
ADDIU sp, sp, 0x30

.align 16
messageBoxChances:
.halfword 52 //message1
.halfword 103 //message2
.halfword 154 //message3
.halfword 205 //message4
.halfword 256 //make sure last value in table is 256 (0x100)
.word 0x00000000 //end list


.align 16
messageTextPtrs:
.word message1
.word message2
.word message3
.word message4
.word message5
.word 0x00000000 //end list
 
.align 16
message1:
.ascii "Good choice"
.byte 0xC2 ; 
.byte 0xFF,0 ; FF=Pause
 
.align 16
message2:
.ascii "Done and done"
.byte 0xC2 ;
.byte 0xFF,0 ; FF=Pause
 
.align 16
message3:
.ascii "This oughta be good"
.byte 0xC2 ;
.byte 0xFF,0 ; FF=Pause
 
.align 16
message4:
.ascii "You got it"
.byte 0xC2 ;
.byte 0xFF,0 ; FF=Pause
 
.align 16
message5:
.ascii "Youre the boss"
.byte 0xC2 ;
.byte 0xFF,0 ; FF=Pause
